rComments: Learnt a lot. Probably the most knowledgeable professor I have faced so far. Open to questions and can answer almost all the questions. Her TA was awesome too. Fair grader. The course is not that difficult for the ones having some background on data communication technologies. Caring and awesome. Loved it.

I had a tough time in the beginning of the course, and somehow made my way through all the assignments. Midterm was tough, but graded leniently; finals was graded super leniently and the final grade stunned me. Prof. Mel is very caring, and gives really amazing lectures; I learnt a lot from her course.
She is very helpful to students. Helps out before the midterm and the final. Very generous to grade most of the time. I recommend you take her class, you will actually learn somethings.

really not accessible outside of class nor inspirational, rarely replies to emails, hard midterm but very easy final exam, scares the students by not telling anything about the tests and gives false information, TA was better in teaching, project so unclear the students gives up. Ended up with a decent grade but would not take again due to stress

Networking was not my major study field, but then I found the classes and materials are really nice and everything explained clearly in class. Professor Melike Erol-Kantarci is patient and always available for answering questions.
She is so beautiful, so caring, love to help and very nice.

Professor is very helpful , she will help her best to solve any doubts. Good grading criteria so that students can achieve holistic development. One of the best professor of university of ottawa students can learn about new research areas and last but not the least amazing and interactive lectures. So it is important to attend lectures.
